40
00:03:03,081 --> 00:03:08,900
Scott: But it's actually, like, a really good platforming, sort of "Ninja Guy" Danish kind of thing.

41
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:11,485
Rym: I mean, the way I would look at these is, remember "Passage"?

42
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:18,660
Rym: We talked a lot about it and how, you know, there's games that exist that kind of blur the line between, I guess, game versus art.

43
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:22,279
Rym: You know, a game that is not just a game or a test of skill.

44
00:03:22,380 --> 00:03:23,720
Scott: Well, any game is art, you know.

45
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,180
Scott: It's like any movie is art, even a really bad one.

46
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:35,360
Rym: Games are primarily either tests of a skill or idle enjoyments, but then there are games... It's kind of like the difference between a film and a movie or a book and literature.

47
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:48,414
