Rym: Scott was like, "It's kind of like the Jenga that's teetering, teetering, teetering,

1629
01:28:39,537 --> 01:28:39,899
Rym: teetering.".

1630
01:28:40,241 --> 01:28:43,180
Rym: And I looked at it, and I went, and it fell right over.

1631
01:28:43,941 --> 01:28:50,439
Rym: So we walk out, this walk of shame, and as I look back, the energy of the room has not diminished at all.

1632
01:28:51,263 --> 01:28:53,437
Rym: I am just older than I used to be.

1633
01:28:54,323 --> 01:28:57,660
Scott: Even though the average age of PAX is more our age than young punk kids.

1634
01:28:57,860 --> 01:29:06,840
Rym: But at the same time, as I walked out, I saw other people our age, and I saw one person who I'm pretty sure was younger than me, also on their way out.

1635
01:29:07,200 --> 01:29:11,415
Scott: Also, I point out, they have, one good thing about PAX is that the concerts are general admission.

1636
01:29:11,760 --> 01:29:15,540
